/**
 * Static navigation index for the Ctrl+K search palette.
 *
 * Entry shape:
 *   id       - stable unique key (also used as the cmdk item value)
 *   title    - primary label shown in the palette
 *   url      - bare pathname, never pre-encoded with ? or #
 *   tab      - optional ?tab= value, resolved by buildHref
 *   hash     - optional #anchor id, resolved by buildHref (requires the target
 *              page to render that id AND call useHashScroll)
 *   section  - display-only breadcrumb shown next to the title
 *   icon     - lucide component reference (this is why the index is .js, not .json)
 *   group    - key of SEARCH_GROUPS
 *   keywords - extra search terms; matched by Fuse, NOT by cmdk's own filter
 *
 * Keyword convention: write what a confused user types, not what the feature is
 * called. "talk to human" and "running out" earn their place; "leads" on the
 * Leads entry does not, since the title already covers it. Multi-word phrases
 * are fine — Fuse runs with ignoreLocation, so it matches anywhere in the string.
 *
 * Known ceiling: keywords only relate phrasings someone thought of in advance.
 * The planned fix is offline semantic search — embed each entry at build time,
 * ship the vectors as static JSON, score cosine similarity in the browser. That
 * buys "how do I stop it replying at night" -> Chatbot Instructions with nothing
 * hand-written. Deliberately deferred: at this index size curated keywords plus
 * the fuzzy fallback in SearchCommand still catch more than they miss, and a
 * build step plus shipped vectors is real weight to carry. Revisit when this
 * array is in the hundreds, or when misses start showing up in analytics.
 */
